Hi @gpbmike ,

Do you set the initial value to false? 

``` js
<MyCheckBox value={false}/>
```

If so it should work. The `'value' in this.props` only checks if the key "value" exists in props, not if the value is "truthy".

The reason behind '' is that you can really create any element. If a checkbox has its value by default false, there is no way for Formsy to understand that. You kinda have to tell it by passing a default "false" value. What you get back though is lots of flexibility in what kind of form elements you want to build :-) 

Example of checkbox:

``` js
var MyCheckbox = React.createClass({
  mixins: [Formsy.Mixin],
  changeValue: function (event) {
    this.setValue(!this.getValue());
  },
  render: function () {
    return (
      <div>
        <input type="checkbox" checked={this.getValue()} onChange={this.changeValue}/>
      </div>
    )
  }
});

<MyCheckBox name="foo" value={false}/>
```

I can't get required validation to work with version 0.12.2 eg.

```
<Input name="myInput" required />
```

The form is valid even though the input (a textbox) is empty.

Current work-around is just to implement an isRequired validation rule and use that instead.

```
Formsy.addValidationRule('isRequired', function(values, value) {
  return typeof value !== 'undefined' && value !== '' && value !== false;
});
```

Thanks. That confirms my suspicions. 

I actually have a work around much like what you are describing. I made my own method to set server errors,

``` js
  setServerErrors: function(errors) {
    var form = this.refs.formsy;

    Object.keys(form.inputs).forEach(function (name, index) {
      var component = form.inputs[name];
      var args = [{
        _isPristine: true,
        serverError: errors[name]
      }];
      component.setState.apply(component, args);
    });
  },
```

And then I can explicitly check for `isPristine() && this.state.serverError` in the input.

Notice I don't set `_isValid` to false like setInputValidationErrors since I thought the user should be able to submit the form again in this case.

