Hmm .. just not setting isValid in updateInputsWithError is not enough. You run into this,

``` js
if (validation.isValid && component.state._externalError) {
  validation.isValid = false;
}
```

It seems to me we're discussing whether server errors / external errors make a field invalid and therefore make the form invalid. Perhaps best is to delegate that to the Mixin (as it is already required that it is used to implement an Input). We'd replace _isValid on the input with isValid(). That way, it is very easy to choose which way it should work. Here is some rough code, 

``` js
// rename updateInputsWithError to setExternalErrors
  setExternalErrors: function (errors) {
    Object.keys(this.inputs).forEach(function (name, index) {
      this.inputs[name].setExternalError(errors[name]);
    }.bind(this));
  }
```

and in the Mixin would be implemented like this,

``` js
setExternalError(error) {
  this.setState({
    _externalError: error
  });
},

setValidationError(error) {
  this.setState({
    _validationError: error
  });
},

isValid: function() {
  !!this.state._validationError || !!this.state._externalError
},

getErrorMessage() {
  this.state._externalError || this.state.validationError
},
```

then I could override isValid to not consider external errors, 

``` js
isValid: function() {
  !!this.state._validationError
}
```

