Sorry about all of the comments.  I figured out how to do what I wanted.  I also found some of this in the docs, after I had figured it out.  I just did not know where to look.  Just for anyone else that is trying to do the same thing and stumbles across this issue.  

The following code will:
- Run validation once the value in the field is valid causing the form to show valid and running any reactive updates.  In my case, enabling the submit button.
- Run validation again if the field then becomes invalid causing the form to show invalid and again disabling the submit button.

```
var TextField = class TextField extends Component {
    render() {
        var {onChange, ...props} = this.props;

        return <FormsyText ref="field" onChange={onChangeWrapper.bind(this)} {...props} />

        function onChangeWrapper(ev) {
            var value = ev.target.value;
            var field = this.refs.field;
            field.isValidValue(value) ? field.setValue(value) : field.isValid() && field.setValue(value);
            onChange && onChange.call(this, ev);
        }
    }
};
```

